title: Water and sewerage rates for businesses

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content: You’ll have to pay for any water your business uses, and for the drainage of water and effluent (liquid waste) from your premises.
chunks.plain_content:
Water and sewerage rates for businesses
You’ll have to pay for any water your business uses, and for the drainage of water and effluent (liquid waste) from your premises.

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content: Ofwat regulates the water industry in England and Wales. There are different regulators in Scotland and Northern Ireland.
chunks.plain_content:
Water and sewerage rates for businesses
Ofwat regulates the water industry in England and Wales. There are different regulators in Scotland and Northern Ireland.

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content:
You’ll be charged either:

  • for the water you use, plus a set charge (if you’ve got a meter)
  • a set amount, usually based on the value of your property

Your business could be eligible for a large user tariff, meaning your water might be cheaper. This is because it often costs less to supply larger businesses.
chunks.plain_content:
Water and sewerage rates for businesses
How you’ll be charged
You’ll be charged either:

  for the water you use, plus a set charge (if you’ve got a meter)
  a set amount, usually based on the value of your property

Your business could be eligible for a large user tariff, meaning your water might be cheaper. This is because it often costs less to supply larger businesses.

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content:
You’ll be charged for any ‘foul sewerage’ (such as wastewater from a toilet or kitchen) and drainage from your property. The amount you pay is usually linked to how much water you use.

You’ll also have to pay for any effluent (liquid waste) you produce. Effluent is water contaminated with things like:

  • fats, oils and grease
  • chemicals
  • food waste

The amount your water supplier will charge is usually based on the amount and strength of the effluent before it reaches the sewer.

You’ll be charged for any ‘foul sewerage’ (such as wastewater from a toilet or kitchen) and drainage from your property. The amount you pay is usually linked to how much water you use.
You’ll also have to pay for any effluent (liquid waste) you produce. Effluent is water contaminated with things like:

  chemicals
  food waste

The amount your water supplier will charge is usually based on the amount and strength of the effluent before it reaches the sewer.

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content: Sewerage charges can either appear on your water bill or your effluent bill, depending on your supplier.
chunks.plain_content:
Water and sewerage rates for businesses
Sewerage charges can either appear on your water bill or your effluent bill, depending on your supplier.

heading_context: Water and sewerage rates for businesses
chunks.html_content:
You may be able to choose your water and sewerage service provider depending on where your business is.

In England and Wales you can check with Ofwat whether you can choose your own supplier.

In Scotland choose your supplier from the Water Commission’s list of suppliers.

In Northern Ireland you can’t choose your own supplier - water is supplied by Northern Ireland Water.
